    • and

      public <OtherTag,​ ResultTag> TaggedPredicate<ResultTag,​Domain> and​(TaggedPredicate<OtherTag,​Domain> other, BiFunction<Tag,​OtherTag,​ResultTag> tagAnd)
      Logical And for TaggedPredicates. Leaves this and the given predicate untouched.
      Type Parameters:
      OtherTag - The type of the other predicate's tag.
      ResultTag - The type of the resulting predicate's tag.
      Parameters:
      other - Another predicate that should be conjuncted with this one.
      tagAnd - And operator for the tags. Since both tags may have different types, we need a function that composes them. Typically, this function should be a description of the kind a and b.
      Returns:
      A predicate that returns true iff both this predicate and the given predicate return true.
      See Also:
      Predicate.and(java.util.function.Predicate<? super T>)

    • and

      public static <Domain> TaggedPredicate<String,​Domain> and​(TaggedPredicate<String,​Domain> a, TaggedPredicate<String,​Domain> b)
      Specialization of and(TaggedPredicate, BiFunction) for Strings. The returned predicate's tag is the string composition of both given tags with an "and" in between and brackets.

      public static <Tag,​ Domain> TaggedPredicate<Tag,​Domain> Any​(Tag tag)

      Type Parameters:
      Tag - The type of the tag.
      Domain - The type of the input of the given predicate (although values of that type are never inspected).
      Parameters:

      Returns:
